<div id="help_regexp" class="hide">

<p>
The data discovery page supports regular expressions in input for for
processed datasets. Just visit
<a href="_navigator?userMode=user">Navigator</a>
and use bottom part of the form.
</p>

<p>
The two keywords are supported:
<ul>
<li><b>regexp:</b> </li>
<li><b>not regexp:</b> </li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
After specifying one of them you can type your favorite regular
expression to look up desired dataset. For example to look up all datasets
whose name has RelVal and RECO you will type
</p>
<ul>
<li>
<pre>
regexp:RelVal.*RECO
</pre>
</ul>
<p>
Complementary to lookup all datasets whose name does not contain RelVal and RECO
you will use second keyword:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
<pre>
not regexp:RelVal.*RECO
</pre>
</li>
</ul>

<p>
Please be aware that regular expression are expensive operation to place. The
lookup is done based on LIKE match with regular expression.
</p>

